The paper deals with the problem of optimal transport, which is a fundamental problem in many areas of computer science, including machine learning, computer vision, and operations research. The paper presents a graph-theoretic approach to approximate optimal transport with additive errors, which is a problem that falls under the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), computational geometry (cs.CG), and information theory (cs.IT).
